23:11.593 --> 23:12.494
He is the good shepherd.

23:16.078 --> 23:17.799
Like the sheep, do you recognize his face?

23:18.820 --> 23:19.281
You should.

23:19.321 --> 23:23.505
He's gone through great lengths to talk to you.

23:23.965 --> 23:25.106
He's gone through great.

23:25.218 --> 23:27.701
He'll go around the world to find you.

23:29.703 --> 23:30.724
There's no escaping God.

23:34.449 --> 23:40.195
Psalm 139, seven through 10, reads, where can I go from your spirit?

23:40.736 --> 23:42.498
Where can I flee from your presence?

23:43.659 --> 23:46.362
If I go up to the heavens, you are there.

23:48.024 --> 23:50.027
If I make my bed in the depths, you are there.

23:51.088 --> 23:53.010
If I rise in the wings of the dawn,

23:53.378 --> 23:58.106
If I settle on the far side of the sea, even there your hand will guide me.

23:58.747 --> 24:00.750
Your right hand will hold me fast.

24:02.253 --> 24:03.334
So you can't escape God.

24:06.339 --> 24:10.626
If you accept them, he's there for comfort and guidance, not condemnation.

24:18.740 --> 24:20.082
Here's a hard one to understand.

24:23.074 --> 24:24.056
You didn't even choose Him.

24:24.256 --> 24:24.897
He chose you.

24:24.917 --> 24:27.661
Isn't it amazing?

24:27.881 --> 24:28.462
He chose us.

24:33.129 --> 24:35.593
John 15, 16 says, you did not choose me.

24:35.613 --> 24:37.356
See, it's not my words, it's the Bible.

24:38.518 --> 24:40.421
You did not choose me, but I chose you.

24:40.441 --> 24:45.088
And I pointed you so that you might go and bear fruit.

24:46.570 --> 24:47.571
Fruit that will last.

24:48.853 --> 24:51.858
And so that whatever you ask in my name, the Father will kill you.

24:53.570 --> 24:54.311
He chose you.

24:55.353 --> 25:01.522
If you're saved and you know Christ, He's not looking for you to sit around and do status quo.

25:04.046 --> 25:09.153
He's looking for you to work for Him to change lives, to change your life, to spread the word.

25:09.194 --> 25:22.834
Again, if your only relationship with Christ and God is just coming on Sundays, there's a lot more to it than that.

25:31.650 --> 25:33.473
From birth until death, he chases you.

25:34.675 --> 25:37.419
We all know the story that beef on the cross.

25:37.479 --> 25:38.240
I love this story.

25:39.181 --> 25:39.943
It's never too late.

25:42.266 --> 25:44.229
So how has God been chasing you?

25:44.249 --> 25:50.358
Have you ever pursued something?

25:52.121 --> 25:56.187
You know, when you really want something, you pursue it, all right?

25:58.931 --> 26:00.754
And you pursue it

26:02.818 --> 26:04.020
relative to how much you want.

26:05.622 --> 26:06.683
You know, we all lose things.

26:07.985 --> 26:08.706
I'll get another one.

26:10.508 --> 26:15.114
But if it's precious to you, you look for it.

26:19.359 --> 26:29.272
You know, there's a lot of married couples here, and there's some newlyweds here, and I can probably ask you about your courtship.

26:29.292 --> 26:30.994
When you want somebody, you quarter them.

26:32.194 --> 26:33.736
You know, man, always be courting.

26:35.157 --> 26:37.099
Even if it's 20 years, always be courting.

26:38.781 --> 26:45.789
But remember how long and how much effort we put into the courtship?

26:47.471 --> 26:49.473
In my case, my wife pursued me for months.

26:52.837 --> 26:53.518
Yeah, I know.

26:54.399 --> 26:55.400
My kids laugh at that too.

26:55.420 --> 26:55.900
They know better.

26:57.682 --> 27:00.946
But I remember the effort that I made to pursue my wife.

27:07.010 --> 27:09.493
You go through great lengths for what you want.

27:12.416 --> 27:15.679
God loves you more than you can imagine.

27:15.739 --> 27:26.151
You take that pursuit, you might have your spouse, you magnify it infinitely, and that's how much love God has for you.

27:28.133 --> 27:29.675
So what will He do for you?

27:31.136 --> 27:32.818
We'll pursue you to the ends of the world.

27:36.322 --> 27:38.064
I asked you earlier, have you ever been lost?

27:39.747 --> 27:42.190
Well, I asked you now, have you ever lost something very precious to you?

27:42.651 --> 27:43.552
What would you do with that?

27:45.355 --> 27:48.960
You know, many of us have kids here or nieces, nephews.

27:50.522 --> 27:52.004
God forbid a kid gets lost.

27:53.707 --> 27:54.287
What would you do?

27:54.307 --> 27:59.114
I know that I would not stop looking for my kid if he got lost.

28:00.336 --> 28:02.599
I would search to the ends of the world.

28:03.641 --> 28:04.562
I would never give up.

28:06.370 --> 28:07.392
He's never going to give up on you.

28:20.172 --> 28:21.915
I know a lot of games today were short in time.

28:21.975 --> 28:24.559
I don't want to drag this on, but I want to share another story with you.

28:28.245 --> 28:31.270
This story, how the helmet haven't pursued me.

28:31.390 --> 28:33.714
You see, when I first came to this church,

28:34.530 --> 28:39.755
And it's funny because it's not another brother about how, you know, you invite people and some stay, some go.

28:40.636 --> 28:41.857
Some are like, whoa, what is this?

28:43.339 --> 28:46.282
When I first came here, I was like, whoa, what is this?

28:46.522 --> 28:47.123
Let's get out of here.

28:49.825 --> 28:52.108
My wife was blessed enough to find this church first.

28:52.168 --> 28:53.189
You're assigned to silver.

28:54.050 --> 28:56.192
Our daughter, Cherise, going to school, you know, the story.

28:56.232 --> 29:02.578
She had the courage, discernment in the Holy Spirit.

29:03.266 --> 29:05.870
to know when and how to witness.

29:07.873 --> 29:14.323
And what would be unheard of nowadays, a public school teacher witnessed to my wife, and she came to church.

29:16.186 --> 29:19.972
You gotta see, before this, we were very lost.

29:21.615 --> 29:25.200
We were both in the world, and you know what the world has to offer?

29:27.123 --> 29:31.570
What seems to be a lot of entertainment, certainly a lot of partying,

29:32.738 --> 29:42.849
And when I heard that my girlfriend who was dating at the time wanted to stop dating and come to church, unheard of.

29:44.411 --> 29:45.532
What are you talking about?

29:45.873 --> 29:47.374
So I came to check it out.

29:47.394 --> 29:50.398
A couple of remembers.

29:52.680 --> 30:01.650
To me, it was unheard of to come to church Mondays, Wednesdays, Thursdays lunch, Friday night group, and then Sunday.

30:02.370 --> 30:03.071
What in the world?

30:04.653 --> 30:07.396
Now, of course, as a young man, I had no problem going to the gym every day.

30:07.416 --> 30:08.878
I don't work out every day.

30:08.898 --> 30:10.980
I had no problem going to work every day.

30:11.882 --> 30:16.948
I had no problem playing sports every day, but going to church every day.

30:17.669 --> 30:19.731
That was something else.

30:19.751 --> 30:23.836
You see, in the world, we have no problem trying to feed our minds.

30:24.597 --> 30:26.679
People go to school forever, some of them.

30:27.741 --> 30:32.146
We have no problem feeding our bodies, some more than others.

30:32.770 --> 30:37.975
We have no problem taking care of our bodies, going to the gym, looking good.

30:41.639 --> 30:46.924
But food for the soul, you don't get, except right here.

30:46.984 --> 30:52.930
This is the only way you can work out your spirit, your soul.

30:54.111 --> 30:56.533
But again, when I first came to church, I'm like, let's get out of here.

30:59.316 --> 31:01.298
So I ran away.

31:02.818 --> 31:13.933
At that time, I had a desire to look for my earthly father because, you know, like many people in this country come from a divorced family.

31:13.973 --> 31:15.315
So I was raped by a single mom.

31:15.916 --> 31:20.542
But, you know, when you don't know your father, you're searching.

31:20.902 --> 31:22.665
And I always thought, wow, it'd be nice to get to know him.

31:24.407 --> 31:25.368
Get his side of the story.

31:26.390 --> 31:32.658
So when I couldn't pull my wife out of this cult that I thought at the time, I'm like, I'm out of here.

31:32.930 --> 31:36.756
I had a friend that was going to Mexico, Nicaragua, and El Salvador.

31:37.397 --> 31:43.726
He did that every year as part of his radio campaign, and he says, hey, because if you don't look for your dad to come with me, I'm going to Nicaragua.

31:44.227 --> 31:44.548
Sure.

31:46.611 --> 31:52.880
Back then, as a side note, I had a very good mortgage business, so I donated money to different things, certainly not from my heart.

31:52.980 --> 31:55.284
It was just to get the tax right off.

31:55.304 --> 31:59.410
One of the places I donated was one of my co-workers, dads,

32:00.642 --> 32:03.446
Christian school that he told us about, I wasn't paying attention.

32:04.968 --> 32:07.211
But this little Christian place was in Nicaragua.

32:08.813 --> 32:10.936
So in the back of my mind, I'm like, why am I going to see my dad?

32:12.258 --> 32:15.142
But I might as well go check out this place, see if my money ever did anything.

32:17.365 --> 32:21.871
So I went to the school, not a school like here.

32:23.694 --> 32:26.738
The school was school for the homeless kids.

32:28.034 --> 32:34.504
And you've all been to Mexico or Tijuana, and you see, you look at cell checklets, just cell things, these kids have no home.

32:35.946 --> 32:47.785
Their school was basically at a dumpster because in Nicaragua, a lot of squatters don't squat homes, but they squat land, and the government allows them to squat in this big dumpster.

32:48.706 --> 32:54.295
So these kids had a habit of going to dumpster for a lot of things, and they'd resell some of it.

32:54.315 --> 32:56.338
They would paint things and try to sell it.

32:57.346 --> 32:57.907
I didn't know that.

33:00.971 --> 33:03.014
All I knew is there's a lot of school that was gonna stop buying.

33:05.357 --> 33:11.725
When I first went to the school, I walk in, even though they have nothing, they have nothing.

33:13.107 --> 33:18.254
I walk into this classroom, I see like these banners, I'm like, what in the world?

33:18.294 --> 33:19.015
Who are they having over here?

33:19.035 --> 33:23.781
It's like this president's becoming, they have this welcome thing everywhere with my name on it.

33:25.423 --> 33:27.346
They have drawings that were, these kids have been,

33:27.714 --> 33:29.036
drawing for me.

33:29.096 --> 33:30.818
Did he know who I was?

33:33.001 --> 33:41.453
You know, over the years, I saved a few of them just to remind myself of my salvation because, see, if the video couldn't put a couple of these up there, it seemed a little bit easier.

33:41.493 --> 33:43.476
This one says 2005.

33:43.556 --> 33:55.292
So in 2005, this year, my salvation, these are little postcards and they look nice here, but each one of these, if you look at the back of them, it's cardboard from the junkyard.

33:55.332 --> 33:56.914
And then they would take

33:57.890 --> 33:58.411
and drawn.

33:59.973 --> 34:01.835
Each of these kids did that for me.

34:04.438 --> 34:08.644
Because you see, they knew it was coming and God knew it was not saved.

34:10.826 --> 34:18.095
God changed me to another country to remind me that even though I was running away from him, he was right there.

34:18.115 --> 34:23.642
I cried.

34:23.662 --> 34:26.546
I knew how to come to the Lord.

34:26.882 --> 34:29.786
When I came back, Sylvia was like, hey, you want to come talk to me?

34:29.866 --> 34:30.227
I'm like, yeah.

34:32.730 --> 34:34.012
And I gave myself to Christ.

34:35.755 --> 34:36.716
I was priming ready.

34:38.899 --> 34:42.805
I always have the Lord found me in Nicaragua, and I declared it here in front of Sylvia.

34:42.865 --> 34:47.391
You see, my biggest obstacle is that I thought I was saved.

34:47.471 --> 34:48.473
I didn't think I was lost.

34:49.194 --> 34:55.122
After all, I was raised a Catholic, which might have been my biggest obstacle, because

34:57.410 --> 35:03.897
You give me somebody who's non-believer, and like Charlie Kirk, I'll talk them until they believe.

35:04.618 --> 35:10.765
Because when you have a clean slate, you don't believe in anything, it's easy to show you where God is.

35:12.587 --> 35:18.453
But when you think you know God, because you're in a different religion, it's hard to open your eyes.

35:19.795 --> 35:23.859
I want to remind you, Christ never said, be a Catholic, a Buddhist or this or that.

35:23.939 --> 35:26.642
No, religion is not what it's about.

35:27.746 --> 35:29.689
It's about your relationship with Christ.

35:32.653 --> 35:40.084
And see, it wasn't until I actually read the book, because even as a Catholic, you recognize the book.

35:41.506 --> 35:44.931
And you read the book and you see where it says that you must be saved.

35:45.952 --> 35:47.054
How could you not want to?

35:48.396 --> 35:50.659
Yes, as a kid, I had some water sprinkled on me.

35:50.699 --> 35:54.544
Yes, as a young adult teenager, I did some confirmation thing.

35:54.564 --> 35:55.666
I had no idea what I did.

35:56.098 --> 36:04.371
But I never truly said Christ, I want you to be the Lord and Savior of my life until that day.

36:11.523 --> 36:12.364
I know my time's up.

36:13.186 --> 36:13.967
Somebody wrap it up.

36:14.989 --> 36:20.498
But before I do, let me ask you, do you know Christ?

36:22.120 --> 36:23.282
If you know Christ,

36:25.282 --> 36:31.149
should today be a reminder of what a great length he went through to find you.

36:31.189 --> 36:38.118
All the seeds that were planted, all the folks that worked for you, all the prayers that came.

36:38.138 --> 36:44.406
He wants you to come as you are.

36:44.446 --> 36:54.578
Whether you're a Catholic, a Protestant, a Baptist, a Buddhist, or an atheist, he wants you to come as you are.

36:58.818 --> 37:03.222
If you're saved, be thankful.

37:03.242 --> 37:03.943
And go to work.

37:04.264 --> 37:04.804
Get to work.

37:05.525 --> 37:06.926
Spread the word that you want you to.

37:06.966 --> 37:10.230
It's not status quo.

37:10.250 --> 37:11.911
It's not about sitting around here on Sundays.

37:13.093 --> 37:13.993
Share your story.

37:14.154 --> 37:15.335
I love to tell my story.

37:15.715 --> 37:18.999
Like this song says, I love to tell the story.

37:21.161 --> 37:26.386
And if you don't get no Christ, perhaps today you need to be carried.

37:29.410 --> 37:30.351
You want to be found?

37:31.553 --> 37:35.037
He's not stopping until he finds you.

37:36.739 --> 37:37.360
This wasn't prayer.

37:39.082 --> 37:45.270
Heavenly Father, I'm so thankful that you found me.

37:45.290 --> 37:46.491
I'm thankful you're here, Lord.

37:47.653 --> 37:51.237
But most of all, Lord, I'm thankful for those that you're still searching for.

37:51.277 --> 37:55.002
For those you have not yet found and pray for them, Lord.

37:55.042 --> 37:58.546
For our friends and our family, they may someday have their eyes open as well.

37:59.266 --> 37:59.764
Amen.

